overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a sleep questionnaire
  application by adding data persistence and an administrative interface. The
  core intent was to store questionnaire responses in a database, provide a
  dashboard for clients to access this data, and secure it with authentication.
  The agent evaluated the existing codebase, which already had a functional
  questionnaire and PDF generation, but lacked database integration and an admin
  panel. Key decisions included using NeonDB (PostgreSQL) for the database,
  implementing a simple password-based authentication system, and combining
  specified demographic fields. The implementation involved updating data
  models, creating API endpoints for saving and retrieving responses (including
  CSV export), building a login page and a dashboard, and integrating the
  database save into the questionnaire submission flow. All necessary files and
  configurations were detailed and implemented to achieve these goals.
